Hypothesis 1

friends_vs_happiness <- responses %>%
select(Number.of.friends, Happiness.in.life) %>%
arrange(desc(Number.of.friends))

head(friends_vs_happiness)
##   Number.of.friends Happiness.in.life
## 1                 5                 5
## 2                 5                 5
## 3                 5                 4
## 4                 5                 4
## 5                 5                 4
## 6                 5                 2
xyplot( Number.of.friends ~ Happiness.in.life, data = friends_vs_happiness, main="", jitter.x=TRUE, jitter.y=TRUE)

Summary Of Results

From the data, it seems as though as Slovakian youth gain more friends, their happiness also increases.

Hypothesis 3

happiness_vs_age <- responses %>%
na.omit() %>%
select(Age, Happiness.in.life) %>%
group_by(Age)%>% 
summarise(avg_happiness = mean (Happiness.in.life))

Average Happiness vs.Age

xyplot( avg_happiness ~ Age, data = happiness_vs_age, main="")

Hypothesis 4: Snake Phobias By Age

age_vs_phobia <- responses %>%
select(Age, Snakes)
 xyplot( Snakes ~ Age, data = age_vs_phobia, main="", jitter.x=TRUE, jitter.y=TRUE)

Summary Of Findings

We expected fear of snakes would be age dependent - or more heavily weighted towards a younger populus - however, this is not the case. A higher frequency exists within the 18-22 year old range as a higher quantity of data points were obtained from these age groups.

Hypothesis 5: Movie Preference by Age

thriller_vs_age <- responses %>%
na.omit() %>%
select(Age, Thriller) %>%
group_by(Age)%>% 
summarise(avg_thriller = mean (Thriller))
xyplot( avg_thriller ~ Age, data = thriller_vs_age, groups=avg_thriller, main="")

We plotted how people ranked thriller movies, and grouped it by age. We ultimately found out that as people get older, they tend to value thriller movies more.

Hypothesis 6: Money spent on appearance by weight

weight_vs_clothes <- responses %>%
na.omit() %>%
select(Weight, Spending.on.looks) %>%
group_by(Weight)%>% 
summarise(avg_spend = mean (Spending.on.looks))
xyplot( avg_spend ~ Weight, data = weight_vs_clothes, main="", jitter.x=TRUE, jitter.y=TRUE)

We found here that ones weight doesnt affect how they perceive they spend money on clothing. On average, everyone in the sample, regardless of age, ranked their appearance spending around 3.
